DRY RUN 


SHOWS WHAT HAPPENS WHEN PLAYBOOK IS EXECUTED without executing the actual playbook 

syntax

 ansible-playbook playbook1.yml --check 


PIP

It is a package manager used to install python libraries 

Example: numPy and pandas are samples of python libraries to be installed using "pip" module

Pip must first be installed using in the machine using "yum"


---
- hosts: all
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: install pip
      yum:
        name: pip
        state: present

    - name: installing NumPy
      pip:
        name: NumPy
        state: present


 ansible-playbook playbook1.yml

To remove 

sed -i 's/present/absent/g' playbook1.yml

To check 

 ansible all -a "pip --version" -b

 ansible all -a "NumPy --version" -b

